commit.message:
pa.md (movdf insn): Distinguish between offsettable and nonoffsettable memory locations when...

        * pa.md (movdf insn): Distinguish between offsettable and
        nonoffsettable memory locations when loading/storing a GR.
        (movdi insn): Likewise.  Loading a DImode constant can take
        as many os 4 insns.

From-SVN: r5182

files.patch:
@@ -1355,9 +1355,9 @@
 
 (define_insn ""
   [(set (match_operand:DF 0 "reg_or_nonsymb_mem_operand"
-			  "=fx,*r,Q,?Q,fx,*&r")
+			  "=fx,*r,Q,?o,?Q,fx,*&r,*&r")
 	(match_operand:DF 1 "reg_or_0_or_nonsymb_mem_operand"
-			  "fxG,*rG,fx,*r,Q,Q"))]
+			  "fxG,*rG,fx,*r,*r,Q,o,Q"))]
   "register_operand (operands[0], DFmode)
    || reg_or_0_operand (operands[1], DFmode)"
   "*
@@ -1367,8 +1367,8 @@
     return output_fp_move_double (operands);
   return output_move_double (operands);
 }"
-  [(set_attr "type" "fpalu,move,fpstore,store,fpload,load")

+  [(set_attr "type" "fpalu,move,fpstore,store,store,fpload,load,load")
+   (set_attr "length" "4,8,4,8,16,4,8,16")])
 
 (define_insn ""
